# API Route Conventions

- Export `async function POST(req: Request)` — all routes are POST-only
- Set `export const runtime = "nodejs"` for server-side libs (Cheerio, axios, form-data)
- Parse body with `await req.json()` and validate required fields early
- Return typed JSON: `NextResponse.json<ResponseType>({ ok: true, ... })`
- On error: return `{ ok: false, error: "message" }` with appropriate status (400/500/502)
- Import types from `@/types` for request/response shapes
- Import Contentstack helpers from `@/lib/contentstack`

```typescript
// Pattern
import { NextResponse } from "next/server";
import type { MyRequest, MyResponse } from "@/types";

export const runtime = "nodejs";

export async function POST(req: Request) {
  const body = (await req.json()) as MyRequest;
  if (!body.requiredField) {
    return NextResponse.json<MyResponse>({ ok: false, error: "missing_field" }, { status: 400 });
  }
  // ...
  return NextResponse.json<MyResponse>({ ok: true, data });
}
```
